          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "INTAD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "  The angular distributions were measured at six",
                "energies spanning the entire energy region from 52 to",
                "72 MeV.  Saddle-point model expression of angular",
                "distribution was used to fit the angular distribution",
                "data."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "REL-REF": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "code": "R",
                "subentry_number": null,
                "author": "J.D.BIERMAN+",
                "reference": {
                  "code": "J,PR/C,54,3068,1996",
                  "field": {
                    "reference_type": "J",
                    "reference": {
                      "code": "PR/C",
                      "number": null,
                      "volume": "54",
                      "part": null,
                      "issue": null,
                      "page": "3068"
                    },
                    "date": 1996
                  }
                }
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "-By authors.  Cross sections at other energies were",
                "determined by measuring the fission cross section at",
                "one particular angle and employing the procedure, as",
                "discussed in REL-REF.",
                "It has been shown that there is little change in the",
                "shape of the angular distribution curve over the",
                "barrier region.  Therefore the ratio of the total cross",
                "section to the differential cross section remains",
                "constant or varies slowly over this entire energy",
                "domain.  On the basis of these results, it is clear",
                "that, if the differential cross section is measured",
                "only at this crossover angle, it is possible to",
                "determine total cross section."
              ]
            }
          ],
